This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommendation systems and collaborative filtering. It also involves machine learning techniques such as matrix factorization and deep neural networks, which are commonly used in the Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions challenges in handling diversity between domains and learning complex non-linear relationships, which are relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques, which are relevant to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
